n, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrix de Bardolf was born in 1170, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Bartholomew Foliot in 1184, in Thame, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1170–":"1170–Surnud","1170–1252":"1170–1252","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","1225":"1225","1252":"1252","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","1170":"1170","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Thame, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1170–":"1170–Kuollut","1170–1252":"1170–1252","1185–1225":"1185–1225","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1252":"1252","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","1170":"1170","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Thame, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Waterstoke, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1170–":"1170–Décédée